HEADWORD: Chesstree
<hw>Chess"tree`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>chassis</ets> a framework of carpentry.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A piece of oak bolted perpendicularly on the side of a vessel, to
aid in drawing down and securing the clew of the mainsail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chessy copper</ent>⟦br⟧
